latestPosts.caption:
Smiling and laughing his way through the FIDE World Rapid and Blitz Team Championships 2025 Vidit Gujrathi and his better half Dr. Nidhi Kataria.

Representing Team Hexamind, Vidit went back home with 3 medals - a team silver in rapid, a team bronze in blitz and an individual silver in rapid! 

Speaking to ChessBase India, Vidit said, "I feel quite relaxed during tournaments these days. While the results of the games is still important, the fact that after its all done, I can go back and spend my time with Nidhi after the game, gives me great mental stability." 

We wish the newly married couple continued success in the upcoming tournaments! 

Photo:  Rafal Oleksiewicz/FIDE

latestPosts.caption:
Rethink Chess Trailer finally out featuring Samay Raina, Vidit Gujrathi, and Sagar Shah. 

We shot this in January when chess was at its peak since Gukesh had just won. We were set to release it in February, then “the controversy” hit.

This episode is on chess, we talk about: 
-Why is chess not part of the Olympics yet? 
-Why are there so few women in chess? 
-Will India become a chess superpower? 
-Chess earnings vs other sport earnings

Featuring
@viditchess — Grandmaster, India’s leading chess player
@sagarshahchess — founder of ChessBaseIndia
@maisamayhoon — comedian, chess enthusiast

Episode out on Saturday, 31st May 3:30pm

Thank you @zero1byzerodha for helping us tell stories like this.

#RethinkIndia #ChessRevolution
